         I find the horse to be a big benefit at level 51. Lots of folks complain about arch-lich though. Regular lich works great. It really nice when fear kiting, since when you're not moving you're medding. There are certainly concessions too, but all around I think I really enjoy the horse. I haven't got myself to turn off the models yet to try that out just 'cause some of the benefit of the horse is that it looks so cool, especially with skeletal form and carrying a harvester. I bet having a staff of writhing in the other hand would look even cooler. I know, stupid reason, but it's the small joys.</P><P>9K is a lot of cash though, make absolute sure you're completely CHR buffed to at least 110 when you buy it and know that you won't be able to outrun MOBs. Basically it's 9K spent to have a new tool in the arsenal. Probably not as useful as others you could get for less $, but I think they make everything a bit more interesting. </P><P>The best part is that you can put them away when you don't need 'em and pull 'em out again when you do. I often dark, send in the pet, pull up the horse, fear kite, take down the horse, loot, med, repeat.</P><P>I camped Gornit for about 6 weeks to come up with the plat, but also went from 45-47 in the process.</P><P>Nefariette<BR>51 Heretic<BR>E'ci</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
